Task 9: Analyze Your Image with Docker Scout

This is where you prove your image is production-ready.
As a DevOps professional, security is a "Shift Left" priority. 
I analyzed my image to identify and mitigate vulnerabilities.

Security Posture Report:
I executed a vulnerability scan using Docker Scout:
docker scout quickview <your-username>/sample-app:v1.0

Get the details:
docker scout cves <your-username>/sample-app:v1.0 > scout_report.txt


Analysis & Remediation:
Observation: Because I used a Multi-Stage build with a Slim/Alpine base in Task 4,
the number of vulnerabilities was significantly lower than standard images.
Action: I ensured the base image was updated to the latest patch version to resolve high-severity CVEs identified in the report.
